## Terminal goal — RIBOZYME row in 16-cell matrix

RIBOZYME 은 4 disease class 각각 catalytic RNA design. Meta `.roadmap.hexa_bio` §0 의 **R 행**.

| Cell  | Disease       | 후보 ribozyme (예)                                       |
|-------|---------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|
| R·α   | AML           | FLT3-ITD 또는 NPM1c mutant mRNA cleavage                 |
| R·β   | SCD           | β-globin precursor trans-splicing 교정                    |
| R·γ   | pan-cov       | conserved viral RNA region cleavage                       |
| R·δ   | senolytic     | SASP key mRNA (예: IL-6) cleavage                        |

**Cell DoD**: in-silico ribozyme design + k_cat/K_M Eigen-Hammes ceiling margin + 12-nt catalytic core + 4-state reaction ladder + witness → `state/discovery_absorption/registry.jsonl`.

**"in-silico ribozyme design" definition** (lands §STALLED draft 2026-05-06; 3-component pipeline):
1. **Sequence generation** — disease-target mRNA scan + hammerhead/HDV/hairpin substrate-recognition arm proposal (≥ 1 candidate per cell, 12-nt catalytic core fixed; σ(6)=12).
2. **Structure prediction** — 2D fold (MFE / partition-function surrogate; Turner-NN subset already inlined in cycle-24 MVP; full ViennaRNA / Nussinov-Zuker inline port deferred to cycle-26 stretch) + active-site geometry sanity check vs canonical reference (Symons 1981 / Wu-Lai 1989 / Buzayan 1986).
3. **Off-target screen** — host-transcriptome substrate-arm specificity (Hamming / seed-region pool, mirrors WEAVE Π^p_2 verifier v2 pattern). Schema field `off_target_screen` allowed-but-stubbed for v1.

C2 cells delivered (cycle 25) cover (1) at metadata-annotation grade; (2) and (3) are partial-stub and tracked under cycle-26 uplift (G26-RB-3, see §G).

