- **Diffusion limit**: F-RB-3-diffusion-limit / F-RB-3-b / F-RB-3-c

### Sub-falsifier scaffolding (lands §STALLED drafts 2026-05-06; mirrors NANOBOT F-NB-1/F-NB-3 pattern; deadline 2026-09-28 unless noted)

- **F-RB-1-genus** — RIBOZYME genus separates from WEAVE (DNA structural folding) and NANOBOT (mechanical actuation): catalytic bond-breaking event (ΔG_TS measurable, k_cat > 0) absent in sister verbs. Audit = registry diff over cycle-25 C2 rows. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via `_python_bridge/module/sister_genus_audit.py` direct-read; cycle-24 MVP k_cat/K_M=8.33e4 > 0 confirms catalytic event (sister verbs have no k_cat axis). Witness `raw_77_ribozyme_subclause_direct_read_v2`.
- **F-RB-1-b** — σ(6)=12 mapping = active-site catalytic residues (not arm length, not full-molecule length). Audit = corpus re-annotation w/ explicit core-vs-arm split (overlaps F-RB-2-inter-rater protocol). **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via same audit; cycle-24 MVP catalytic_core_nt_count=12 (sequence `CUGAUGAGGCCG`), expected=12.
- **F-RB-1-c** — k_cat/K_M Eigen-Hammes ceiling distinguishes RIBOZYME from non-catalytic RNA aptamers (binding-only ceiling ≤ 10⁹ M⁻¹s⁻¹ with no bond-breaking event). Audit = aptamer null-control corpus n ≥ 10. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via `_python_bridge/module/ribozyme_aptamer_null_corpus.py` — n=10 hand-curated published aptamers (theophylline / ATP / tetracycline / malachite green / L-arginine / aminoglycosides / L-tryptophan / FMN / streptomycin); all k_cat=0 (binding-only); max n6_match=1/4 (only φ binary by accident); lattice correctly REJECTS aptamers as ribozymes → genus distinction confirmed. Witness `raw_77_ribozyme_aptamer_null_corpus_v1`.
- **F-RB-2-inter-rater** — n=30 corpus 30/30 perfect (`log_bf=79.74` cycle 25) requires κ ≥ 0.6 inter-rater agreement (≥ 2 independent reviewers re-score catalytic-core nt count + reaction-state-ladder mapping) before σ(6)=12 promotes from STRUCTURAL-EXACT-CANDIDATE to STRUCTURAL-EXACT. Audit = registry row `raw_77_ribozyme_interrater_v1`. **[SCHEMA LANDED 2026-05-06]** at [`ribozyme/spec/interrater_v1.schema.json`](ribozyme/spec/interrater_v1.schema.json) (draft-07; rater_count, per_axis_kappa, overall_kappa, stratified_log_bf; AND-gate PASS overall_kappa ≥ 0.6 ∧ stratified_log_bf.max < 5.0; validator-conformant via `selftest/json_schema_validator.py`). **[PROVISIONAL AI-AUDIT LANDED 2026-05-06]** at [`_python_bridge/module/ribozyme_interrater_ai_audit.py`](_python_bridge/module/ribozyme_interrater_ai_audit.py) (stdlib only; raw 9 hexa-only). Two independent AI-as-rater heuristic re-scorings (rater A: `paper_ref` keyword/year heuristic; rater B: `ribozyme_class` + `notes` text heuristic, ignoring `paper_ref`) executed against the canonical n=30 corpus. **Result:** `overall_kappa = 0.2007` (macro-mean across 4 axes — `sigma=0.0000` degenerate, `tau=−0.1972`, `phi=0.0000` degenerate, `J2=+1.0000`); `stratified_log_bf {mean=33.53, min=12.72, max=54.34}`; AND-gate **FAIL** (`overall_kappa<0.6`, `stratified_log_bf.max≥5.0`). Witness `raw_77_ribozyme_interrater_v1` (validates against schema). raw_91 honest C3 disclosure embedded inline (`notes` field): AI-rater is NOT equivalent to human raters; full GATE-26-4 / G26-RB-1 closure requires ≥2 external human raters. **Honest finding:** the low AI-rater κ (driven by degenerate marginals on σ/φ axes — both raters near-unanimously assign 1) reinforces the cycle-25 30/30 suspicion that the rubric is rater-dependent. Audit kickoff (≥2 human raters scoring corpus) still tracks G26-RB-1 deadline 2026-06-15. Aligned with meta `.roadmap.hexa_bio` §G GATE-26-4 (κ ≥ 0.6).
- **F-RB-2-c** — corpus-source-bias: stratify n=30 corpus by `paper_ref` year (pre/post 2000 proxy for textbook-vs-experimental); falsified if `|log10_BF(textbook) − log10_BF(experimental)| > 1.0`. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** Implementation `_python_bridge/module/ribozyme_bayesian_n6_stratum_bias.py` (stdlib mirror of nanobot pattern). Result: pre_2000 (n=11, all 4-axis matches 11/11) and post_2000 (n=19, all 4-axis matches 19/19) → match-fraction proxy delta=0.0 → **PASS**. F-RB-2 robust to source-class disaggregation. Witness `raw_77_ribozyme_bayesian_audit_v2` audit_kind=n6_source_class_stratum_bias. Note: both strata at 100% match → log_bf inf both sides; inter-rater uncertainty (G26-RB-1) is the independent axis still pending.
- **F-RB-2-n6-decorative** — n6-strip-ablation: re-evaluate per-axis match thresholds (sigma in [10,15] / tau=4 / phi=2 / J2=True) with perturbed values to test whether F-RB-2 cycle-25 30/30 (log_bf=79.74) is **load-bearing on the canonical thresholds** or **decorative**. PASS gate: `|delta_log10_bf| ≥ 0.5`. Witness: `raw_77_ribozyme_bayesian_audit_v2.f_rb_2_subclauses.f_rb_2_n6_decorative`. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** Implementation `_python_bridge/module/ribozyme_bayesian_n6_ablation.py` (stdlib mirror of nanobot ablation). 5 perturbations tested (shrink_sigma_range / shift_tau_to_5 / shift_phi_to_3 / invert_j2 / all_perturbed); canonical = 30/30 4-axis matches, perturbations collapse the match count → log_bf sentinels move (+inf canonical → -inf or below decisive threshold under perturbation). Δlog10_BF max=1e9 sentinel ≫ 0.5 threshold → **PASS decisive** (canonical thresholds ARE load-bearing on the ribozyme corpus matches).
- **F-RB-3-diffusion-limit** — measured k_cat/K_M ≤ 10⁹ M⁻¹s⁻¹ across all corpus members + simulated MVPs. Audit = registry aggregate over F-RB-2 30 rows + F-RB-4 sim row. Deadline 2026-09-28 (co-runs with F-RB-2 closure). **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via direct-read audit `_python_bridge/module/sister_subclause_direct_read_audit.py`; cycle-24 MVP k_cat/K_M=8.33e4 << 1e9 ceiling (margin 4.08 orders). Witness `raw_77_ribozyme_subclause_direct_read_v1`.
- **F-RB-3-b** — diffusion margin ≥ 1 order-of-magnitude in MVP (cycle-24 measured: 4.08 orders, PASS). Audit = sim-row direct read (`raw_77_ribozyme_kinetics_v1.eigen_hammes_margin_orders`). **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via same direct-read audit (4.08 orders >> 1.0 threshold).
- **F-RB-3-c** — Mg²⁺ dependence sweep (1 / 5 / 10 / 25 mM) preserves Eigen-Hammes margin. Audit = MVP sim parameterised sweep, deferred to cycle 26 if not already in registry. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via `_python_bridge/module/ribozyme_mg_sweep_audit.py` analytic Hill-curve audit (raw_91 honest C3: NOT a full kinetic re-sim — existing ribozyme_kinetics_simulation has MG_MM as metadata only; full Mg²⁺-dependent rates cycle-26+). Hill model n=2, K_Mg=2 mM (Steitz 1993 + Dahm-Uhlenbeck 1991): margins {1 mM: 4.76, 5 mM: 4.13, 10 mM: 4.08, 25 mM: 4.07} orders, all >> 1 threshold → PASS. Witness `raw_77_ribozyme_subclause_direct_read_v3` audit_kind=f_rb_3_c_mg_sweep_analytic.

## F-RB-2 corpus references (lands §STALLED draft 2026-05-06)

n=30 corpus sources for the cycle-25 Bayesian audit (registry row `raw_77_ribozyme_bayesian_audit_v1`, ts 2026-05-05T17:11:50Z; full n=30 list inline in `row.rows[]`).

**Top-5 anchor sources:**
1. Symons 1981 NAR 9:6527 — hammerhead minimal HHR (13 nt; trimmed to 12-nt strictly conserved core).
2. Cech 1982 Cell 31:147 — group-I Tetrahymena intron.
3. Guerrier-Takada / Altman 1983 Cell 35:849 — RNase P M1 RNA.
4. Wu-Lai 1989 PNAS 86:1831 — HDV antigenomic ribozyme.
5. Nissen-Steitz 2000 Science 289:920 — ribosome PTC (50S).

**Scoring rubric (per-axis, applied to each of n=30):**
- σ(6)=12 ∈ [10,15] catalytic-core nt count.
- τ(6)=4 reaction-state ladder (substrate-bound → TS → cleaved → released).
- φ(6)=2 binary outcome (cleaved / uncleaved).
- J₂=24 trigonal-bipyramidal TS pose-equivalence (or +/-5 Å active-site cluster for large ribozymes; raw_91 disclosure).

**raw_91 caveat**: corpus is hand-curated (not live-PubMed-pulled); per-axis match counts + raw_91 disclosure recorded inline in registry row. Reproducibility risk addressed via F-RB-2-inter-rater (G26-RB-1).

